Zimbabwe Earns $293 Million Selling Tobacco in Season So Far, Newsday Says

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-06-15T11:31:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-15/zimbabwe-earns-293-million-selling-tobacco-in-season-so-far-newsday-says.html
Tobacco farmers in  Zimbabwe  have
earned $293 million from sales of the leaf so far this season,
 Newsday reported , citing the Tobacco Industry and Marketing
Board, which regulates the industry.  As of June 13, farmers in the African nation had sold 108.7
million kilograms (240 million pounds) of tobacco, 31 percent
more than a year earlier, the Harare-based newspaper said.  Zimbabwe is likely to produce between 170 million kilograms
and 200 million kilograms of the leaf this season, up from 123
million kilograms last year, Newsday said. The countryâ€™s tobacco
marketing season traditionally runs from March to October.  To contact the reporter on this story:
